Reasoning: The paper deals with the transmission rate and decoding process of codes, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT) and communication (cs.COMM). The use of random code construction and modified asymptotic equipartition property (AEP) theorem also suggests a possible fit in the sub-category of statistical inference (cs.SI). The study of capacity under mismatched decoding may also fall under the sub-categories of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) and cryptography and security (cs.CC).
